verses.text_plain: How amiable are thy tabernacles, O Lord of hosts!
verses.verse_html:
1How amiable are thy tabernacles, O Lord of hosts! ▼
▼ for the sons: or, of the sons

footnotes.body_text: ▼ for the sons: or, of the sons
footnotes.body_html: ▼ for the sons: or, of the sons

verses.text_plain: My soul longeth, yea, even fainteth for the courts of the Lord: my heart and my flesh crieth out for the living God.
verses.verse_html: 2My soul longeth, yea, even fainteth for the courts of the Lord: my heart and my flesh crieth out for the living God.

verses.text_plain: Yea, the sparrow hath found an house, and the swallow a nest for herself, where she may lay her young, even thine altars, O Lord of hosts, my King, and my God.
verses.verse_html: 3Yea, the sparrow hath found an house, and the swallow a nest for herself, where she may lay her young, even thine altars, O Lord of hosts, my King, and my God.

tokens.text: for herself, where she may lay

verses.text_plain: Blessed are they that dwell in thy house: they will be still praising thee. Selah.
verses.verse_html: 4Blessed are they that dwell in thy house: they will be still praising thee. Selah.

verses.text_plain: Blessed is the man whose strength is in thee; in whose heart are the ways of them.
verses.verse_html: 5Blessed is the man whose strength is in thee; in whose heart are the ways of them.

verses.text_plain: Who passing through the valley of Baca make it a well; the rain also filleth the pools.
verses.verse_html:
6Who passing through the valley of Baca make it a well; the rain also filleth the pools. ▼
▼ Baca…: or, mulberry trees make him a well, etc
 , ▼
▼ filleth: Heb. covereth

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Baca…: or, mulberry trees make him a well, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Baca…: or, mulberry trees make him a well, etc

verses.text_plain: They go from strength to strength, every one of them in Zion appeareth before God.
verses.verse_html:
7They go from strength to strength, every one of them in Zion appeareth before God. ▼
▼ strength to…: or, company to company

footnotes.body_text: ▼ strength to…: or, company to company
footnotes.body_html: ▼ strength to…: or, company to company

verses.text_plain: O Lord God of hosts, hear my prayer: give ear, O God of Jacob. Selah.
verses.verse_html: 8O Lord God of hosts, hear my prayer: give ear, O God of Jacob. Selah.

verses.text_plain: Behold, O God our shield, and look upon the face of thine anointed.
verses.verse_html: 9Behold, O God our shield, and look upon the face of thine anointed.

verses.text_plain: For a day in thy courts is better than a thousand. I had rather be a doorkeeper in the house of my God, than to dwell in the tents of wickedness.
verses.verse_html:
10For a day in thy courts is better than a thousand. I had rather be a doorkeeper in the house of my God, than to dwell in the tents of wickedness. ▼
▼ I had…: Heb. I would choose rather to sit at the threshold

footnotes.body_text: ▼ I had…: Heb. I would choose rather to sit at the threshold
footnotes.body_html: ▼ I had…: Heb. I would choose rather to sit at the threshold

verses.text_plain: For the Lord God is a sun and shield: the Lord will give grace and glory: no good thing will he withhold from them that walk uprightly.
verses.verse_html: 11For the Lord God is a sun and shield: the Lord will give grace and glory: no good thing will he withhold from them that walk uprightly.

verses.text_plain: O Lord of hosts, blessed is the man that trusteth in thee.
verses.verse_html: 12O Lord of hosts, blessed is the man that trusteth in thee.
